@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
        At XYZ Supermarket, we take the privacy of our customers seriously. We collect information necessary to provide quality services and enhance the shopping experience. The information we collect includes:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Contact information, such as name, email address, and phone number.</li>
        <li>Payment information, such as credit card details, to process transactions.</li>
        <li>Purchase preferences and browsing habits on our website.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Use of Information</h2>
    <p>
        The collected information is used to:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Process transactions and fulfill deliveries.</li>
        <li>Personalize the shopping experience and offer tailored promotions.</li>
        <li>Improve our products and services.</li>
        <li>Send relevant marketing communications, with user consent.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Information Security</h2>
    <p>
        We take measures to protect customer information. We use industry-standard security protocols, symbolized by the lock icon:
        <img src="https://example.com/images/lock-icon.png" alt="Lock Icon">
        , to ensure the confidentiality and integrity of data.
    </p>

    <h2>Sharing Information with Third Parties</h2>
    <p>
        We do not sell, trade, or rent personal information to third parties without user consent. We prioritize collaboration and data protection, as depicted in the image:
        <img src="https://example.com/images/data-protection.png" alt="Colaboración y Protección de Datos">
        , except when necessary to process transactions or comply with legal requirements.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
    <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies, symbolized by the cookie icon:
        <img src="https://example.com/images/cookie-icon.png" alt="Cookie Icon">
        , to enhance navigation and collect information about website usage. Users can manage cookie preferences through browser settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to the Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        We reserve the right to update our Privacy Policy at any time. Significant changes will be notified through our website or via email.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
        For any questions or concerns related to privacy, please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:privacy@supermarketxyz.com">privacy@supermarketxyz.com</a>.
    </p>
</div>
